# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# Fixes #<issue-number>
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Type: feat, fix, perf, docs, test, refactor, chore
# Scope: storage, api, flusher, bench, ci, etc.
# Subject: Imperative mood, lowercase, no period at end (max 50 chars)
#
# Body: Explain WHAT and WHY (not HOW). Wrap at 72 characters.
#       Include:
#       - Rationale for the change
#       - Alternative approaches considered
#       - Performance impact (if applicable)
#       - Breaking changes (if any)
#
# Examples:
#   feat(storage): add QUIC write path
#   fix(flusher): prevent deadlock on concurrent flush
#   perf(rocksdb): batch writes for 30% latency improvement
#   docs(readme): update installation instructions
#
# For large diffs (>200 lines), include justification for new code:
#   Why is this code necessary?
#   Why can't existing code solve this?
#   What alternatives were considered?
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Setup (one-time):
#   git config commit.template .gitmessage
#
# Co-authored-by: Warp <agent@warp.dev>  (if AI-assisted)
